  "why": "The paper goes beyond merely reporting failures: it analyzes where failures occur (e.g., sensitivity to number/kind of transformations, per-dataset/per-model robust-accuracy tables, T3 vs T6) and experiments with model-internal metrics (using neuron-coverage as an alternative fitness and comparing loss-based vs coverage-based fitness). These constitute partial diagnostic insight (characterizing failure patterns and relating the fuzzer’s selections to an internal metric). However, the paper does not trace failures to underlying root causes (no empirical analysis linking failures to corrupted or biased training data, spurious features, or detailed neuron-activation/root-cause explanations). The authors report aggregated and per-model robust-accuracy statistics and evaluate fitness/selection metrics, but do not provide diagnostic analyses that explain why the model relies on non-robust/spurious features or how specific training-data weaknesses cause the observed failures.",
